# Nature's Infusions — Static E‑Store

A small, privacy‑first static storefront for Nature's Infusions. This repository is plain HTML, CSS and vanilla JavaScript with no build step. Focus is on accessibility, semantic HTML and a conservative, reviewable workflow.

## Quick links

- Site entry: [index.html](index.html)
- Store page (products & cart forms): [pages/store.html](pages/store.html)
- Machine product data: [products.json](products.json)
- Main stylesheet: [assets/css/main.css](assets/css/main.css)
- App behaviour & SW registration: [assets/js/app.js](assets/js/app.js)
- Service worker: [service-worker.js](service-worker.js)
- PWA manifest: [manifest.json](manifest.json)
- Offline page: [offline.html](offline.html)
- Privacy note: [privacy.txt](privacy.txt)
- Repository Copilot guidance: [.github/copilot-instructions.md](.github/copilot-instructions.md)
- Contribution prompts: [.github/prompts/refactor-html.prompt.md](.github/prompts/refactor-html.prompt.md)
- Environment variables: [.env](.env) (contains PAYPAL_EMAIL / deployment paths)
- License: [LICENSE](LICENSE)

## TL;DR — what you can safely change

- Small HTML5 refactors and accessibility fixes in pages under `pages/` (see [pages/store.html](pages/store.html) note below).
- Conservative CSS or JS helpers added under `assets/css/` and `assets/js/`.
- Non‑functional docs, meta and metadata updates.

## How to run locally (smoke test)

Serve the site from a local static server so the service worker can register (test on `localhost`):

```sh
```

Verify service‑worker install/uninstall cycles on localhost and check pages:

- [offline.html](offline.html) (offline UX)
- [404.html](404.html)

## Editing & refactor checklist

When editing HTML/CSS/JS follow the repo checklist (see [.github/copilot-instructions.md](.github/copilot-instructions.md)):

- Preserve top-line DOCTYPE and `<html lang="en-AU">` in any edited page.
- Ensure `<meta charset="utf-8">` and `<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1">` are present.
- Prefer semantic landmarks: header, nav, main, article, section, footer.
- Give images meaningful `alt` text (or `role="presentation"` for decorative images).
- Bind `<label for="...">` to form controls for accessibility.
- Keep JS changes scoped to `assets/js/` and CSS to `assets/css/`. Do not alter SW guards in [assets/js/app.js](assets/js/app.js) (e.g. `if (location.protocol === 'https:' || location.hostname === 'localhost') { ... }`).
- Add a one-line inline comment for why a change was made referencing the acceptance checklist.

## Commit & PR guidance (copy into PR body)

- Commit title format: `chore(refactor-html): short summary`
- Include the files changed (mandatory).
- Smoke test performed: `python -m http.server 8000` and SW install/uninstall tested on localhost (yes/no)
- HTML meta & semantics checked: yes/no
- Accessibility basics verified (labels, alt text, form associations): yes/no
- Tools used: list MCP/GitHub/Microsoft tools and key results/links (if used) — see [.github/copilot-instructions.md](.github/copilot-instructions.md)
- Reviewer: [2MuchC0ff33@example.org](mailto:2MuchC0ff33@example.org) (replace before merge)

Example commit body (if touching payments):

```text

Files changed:
- pages/store.html
- products.json

, SW install/uninstall: yes
HTML semantics checked: yes
Accessibility basics: yes
Tools used: mcp_github_github_search_code (found SW registration in assets/js/app.js)
```

## Accessibility & Privacy

- Project is privacy‑first: no analytics or third‑party trackers. See [privacy.txt](privacy.txt).
- Follow the HTML5 refactor checklist in [.github/copilot-instructions.md](.github/copilot-instructions.md).

## Contributing

- Keep changes small and reversible. Edit files directly under repo root, `pages/`, `pages/store/`, `assets/css/partials/`, `assets/js/data/` and `assets/js/modules/`.
- Add new assets only under `assets/` and reference them relatively (no external trackers/CDNs).

## Contact & Authors

- Author / generator credit is embedded in pages (site footer).
